eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 60 Years
Maximum age: 80 Years

Concurrent chemotherapy; patients may be on other non-chemotherapy anti-cancer treatments, per Food and Drug Association (FDA) labeling of radium-223, provided that these are not changed during the primary pain assessment period
Willing and able to provide written informed consent.

Had received active immunosuppressive therapy for graft-versus-host disease (GVHD)
             within 2 weeks before study start
Patients must have been free of disease for a minimum period of 8 weeks, up to a maximum of 3 years following completion of surgery and/or radiotherapy
Women who consented to allow their specimens and clinical data to be used for future cancer research

Any other serious illness or medical condition, such as but not limited to: 
* Any infection >= National Cancer Institute Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events (NCI-CTCAE) version 4.0 grade 2
* Cardiac failure New York Heart Association (NYHA) III or IV 
* Crohn’s disease or ulcerative colitis 
* Bone marrow dysplasia 
* Fecal incontinence
Current smokers (Smoking >= 11 cigarettes per day), as smoking increases metabolism and decreases serum levels of erlotinib
Aspartate aminotransferase (AST) and alanine aminotransferase (ALT) =< 2.5 times ULN (unless elevated due to secondary lymphomatous involvement of the liver)

Patients who are currently receiving other anti-cancer agents or radiation therapy
             are not eligible.

outcome_measures.measure: Incidence second of primary lung tumors

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Will be graphically summarized for the individual patients using a “swimmer plot” to convey the duration of treatment, timing of response and its duration, time until progression and survival. Descriptive statistics (mean, median, and 95% confidence intervals) will be utilized to present the exploratory efficacy results.
outcome_measures.time_frame: Time from registration to death due to any cause, or censored at date last known alive, assessed up to 2 years

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Induction: pre-infusion (0 hr) on Day 1 of Cycle 1; pre-infusion (within 5 hr prior to dose) on Day 1 on Cycle 6; Post-induction: at treatment discontinuation (up to Month 24), 120 days and 1-2 years post-last dose (maximum up to 5 years) (infusion duration: 1-2 days) (1 cycle: 21 days)
outcome_measures.measure: Percentage of Participants with Human Anti-Human Antibodies (HAHAs) to Obinutuzumab
outcome_measures.time_frame: Pre-infusion (0 hr) on Day 1 of Cycle 1 up to maximum 5 years. Detailed timeframe is given in outcome measure description.
